org.xlbean

Interface XlBean

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleXlBeanFactory.SimpleXlBean, XlBeanImpl

    public interface XlBean
extends java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>
    Interface for data store.

    Basic concept of this library is to read or write any value on excel sheet as String, and make it easy to access. This is an interface for the data holder class.

    This class extends Map. The implementation of this interface is intended to hold instances of following classes as values of this map.

    • XlBean
    • List
    • String
    If you want to put any value other than the types above, use set(Object) method which converts any type of object, including Map, List or any other custom classes, to XlBean suitable type.

    Other methods defined in this class are utility to convert Map to other format easily.

      • beanOf

        <T> T beanOf(java.lang.String sourceKey,
             java.lang.Class<T> destinationClass)
        Returns the object of destinationClass filled with the contents mapped from a Map retrieved by sourceKey.

        If an object retrieved by sourceKey is null or not Map instance, then it returns blank instance of destinationClass.

        Mapping from Map of sourceKey to instance of destinationClass is key to property mapping. Refer to BeanConverter for further detail.

        Parameters:
        sourceKey -
        destinationClazz -
        Returns:
